main event: Two unidentified dark elongated objects were observed in the sky over Columbus, Ohio on July 7, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were described as elongated and dark in color., The sighting occurred during the evening at approximately 2045 hours., The objects were reported to have varied in speed and direction., Witnesses mentioned that the objects appeared brighter than blue and showered off sparks., The sighting lasted for about 2 to 5 seconds.
sighted object: two dark elongated objects in the sky
